 {"id":"bd-nqq1d","title":"PORT: __cxa_throw_bad_array_new_length (Itanium C++ ABI bad-array-new stub)","description":"Port the Itanium C++ ABI `__cxa_throw_bad_array_new_length()` entry point. Compilers emit a call to this symbol when a `new T[n]` allocation expression overflows the maximum array length (e.g., `n * sizeof(T)` would exceed SIZE_MAX). Per the ABI, the function never returns; it should throw `std::bad_array_new_length` (a C++ exception). Without an exception runtime we mirror the same fail-stop convention used for `__cxa_pure_virtual`: write a diagnostic to stderr and abort the process. This unblocks linking C++ code that uses array-new expressions. Implementation: thin no_mangle Rust extern "C" fn `-> !` that writes "bad_array_new_length" diagnostic via libc::write to fd 2 and invokes libc::abort(). Test: fork+execute test that calls the function in the child and verifies SIGABRT termination.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T10:52:32.849352863Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:55:26.376604117Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:55:26.374549616Z","close_reason":"shipped: __cxa_throw_bad_array_new_length C++ stub writing diagnostic + abort + 1 fork-based abi test verifying SIGABRT, all green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-nrh5v","title":"P0: setstate overreads untracked caller state buffer","description":"[CRITICAL] frankenlibc-abi::stdlib_abi::setstate treats any untracked non-null pointer as RANDOM_STATE_MAX_BYTES (128) bytes: known_remaining(state).unwrap_or(128), then creates std::slice::from_raw_parts(state, state_len). A valid C caller can pass an 8-byte initstate/setstate buffer (minimum supported by this code and glibc TYPE_0 shape). Stack/static caller buffers are untracked, so setstate(&mut [0u8;8]) constructs a 128-byte slice and frankenlibc_core::stdlib::setstate reads up to 32 words.

Evidence:
- crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/stdlib_abi.rs:2929-2938 defaults untracked state_len to 128 and passes that slice to core.
- crates/frankenlibc-core/src/stdlib/random_sv.rs:160-169 loops over state_buf.len().min(128)/4 and reads every copied word.
- crates/frankenlibc-abi/tests/stdlib_abi_test.rs only rejects tracked short buffers, so untracked short caller buffers are uncovered.

Repro to add as a failing ABI test before fixing:
let mut tiny = [0u8; 8];
unsafe { let _ = frankenlibc_abi::stdlib_abi::setstate(tiny.as_mut_ptr().cast()); }

Expected: do not read beyond the actual caller buffer; parse only a self-describing header/minimal state or reject ambiguous untracked buffers safely. Actual: untracked pointer is assumed to have 128 readable bytes, causing an ABI-boundary OOB read.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"codex-setstate-bounds","created_at":"2026-04-29T02:12:02.507868152Z","created_by":"cod_2_reviewer","updated_at":"2026-04-29T03:18:08.862089092Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T03:18:08.860221476Z","close_reason":"Fixed setstate untracked-buffer overread by bounding ambiguous untracked state buffers to the 8-byte minimum instead of assuming 128 bytes, while remembering untracked initstate buffers by pointer/length for roundtrip restoration. Added ABI regression coverage for an untracked 8-byte stack buffer. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check on touched files; git diff --check on touched files; rch cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test stdlib_abi_test setstate -- --nocapture --test-threads=1 passed; rch cargo test -p frankenlibc-abi --test conformance_diff_stdlib_random -- --nocapture --test-threads=1 passed with 156 calls and 0 divergences; rch cargo check -p frankenlibc-core -p frankenlibc-abi --all-targets passed; rch cargo clippy -p frankenlibc-core -p frankenlibc-abi --all-targets -- -D warnings passed. Workspace cargo fmt --check remains blocked by unrelated conformance_diff_time.rs formatting drift.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
